   Here is the 53-46 roll call by which the
Senate ejected an amendment Wednesday to strengthen smog control
requirements in the compromise clean air bill.
   On this vote, a ``yes'' vote was a vote to table, and in effect
kill, while a ``no'' vote was a vote to keep the amendment alive.
   Voting ``yes'' were 24 Democrats and 29 Republicans.
   Voting ``no'' were 31 Democrats and 15 Republicans.
