   Here is the 59-36 roll call by which the
Senate Wednesday rejected a resolution offered by Sen. Jesse Helms,
R-N.C., urging President Bush immediately to recognize Lithuania as
independent from the Soviet Union.
   On this vote, a ``yes'' vote was a vote in favor of the Helms
resoultion while a ``no'' vote was a vote against it.
   Voting yes were nine Democrats and 27 Republicans.
   Voting no were 44 Democrats and 15 Republicans.
   xxx denotes senators not voting.
